<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-04-13T07:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-04-13T07:00:00-05:00" n="301" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d301">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">760D.6115/48: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-04-13T15:00:00+03:00">April 13,
                                    1940—3 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received April 13—2:45 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>379. The Moscow newspapers publish the text of an act signed at Petsamo
                            on April 9 by representatives of the Red Army and of the Finnish Army,
                            acting in accordance with articles VI and VII of the Protocol appended
                            to the peace treaty between the Soviet Union and Finland, signed March
                            12, effecting the transfer to Finnish authorities of Petsamo and the
                            port of Liinahamari with all buildings and equipment appertaining to
                            municipal economy and local industry.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Steinhardt</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>